\newlabel{fig:main_results}{{1}{5}{\textbf {Main Results: Single-position intervention fails; multi-position succeeds.} (a) Layer sweep: single-position intervention (gray) achieves 0\% transfer at all 28 layers; multi-position intervention (orange) peaks at 96\% at layer 8. (b) Condition comparison at layer 8: \texttt {all\_demo} (96\%) and \texttt {output\_only} (94\%) both succeed; \texttt {input\_only} fails (0\%). (c) Task pair transfer matrix: a cluster of tasks (uppercase, repeat, length) shows high bidirectional transfer (50--100\%)}{figure.caption.10}{}}
